The paper discusses a new key exchange protocol and its practical instances, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The protocol is based on semidirect product of (semi)groups, which involves concepts of information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of a particular non-commutative semigroup, which relates to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and linear algebra (cs.LG).
